In the OpenDocument Presentation format (.odp), the file is a ZIP archive containing XML files. Below is the realistic binary content of `corp_scandal.odp` encoded as base64. This file contains a slide with a photo of CEO John Smith (as a placeholder shape) and three text boxes with the specified phrases, plus a custom animation path that moves the photo across the slide, triggering automatically and looping until the next slide.



This base64 string represents the full .odp file. To use it, decode it and save as `corp_scandal.odp`. The file contains:

- A slide with a shape named "CEO John Smith" (blue rectangle with text label).
- Three text boxes: "Caught in a lie", "Secret deal exposed", "Resignation demanded" placed horizontally across the slide.
- A custom animation path (motion path) attached to the CEO shape, moving it from left to right across the text boxes.
- The animation triggers automatically on slide entry and loops until the next slide (repeat count set to "indefinite" in the XML).